</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,899,1885]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,409,899,925]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
. Head black, infused with brown in middle of lower half of frons and face, paler yellow on genae and underside. Hair short black on black part of frons and shining yellow with scattered golden scales on brown areas of frons and face. Fine silvery scales on occiput behind eyes and with short yellow hairs at margin of cavity. Frons three times width of ocellar triangle at vertex. Eye indentation and bisecting line scarcely indicated. Antenna ratio 
<number box="[433,452,1099,1125]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<number box="[457,469,1099,1125]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[473,492,1099,1125]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[498,517,1099,1125]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
with short black hairs on scape and pedicel, first flagellomere elongate conical, second narrow linear. Proboscis no longer than oral cavity, blackish brown with broad fleshy labellae. Palpi half length of proboscis, brown with brown hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,899,1885]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Thorax black with post­alar calli and scutellum red­brown. Hair yellow­brown on fore margin and anepisternum, brown on metatergites, also a few black hairs intermixed, especially on propleura. Narrow scales on scutum shining brown, paler yellow­brown above wing bases. Bristles black, dense on hind margin of scutellum. Plumula yellow­brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,899,1885]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Legs including coxae dark brown with black bristles. Fore tibiae smooth, for tarsus as long as tibia, claws greatly reduced. 
<collectingCountry box="[689,748,1419,1445]" name="India" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora with a complete row of short robust bristles on underside. Claws black, gently curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,899,1885]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[394,481,1499,1525]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="30.[264,382,290,314]" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Lectotype specimens of species of Bombyliidae referred to in Bezzi’s manuscript. 17 – 18, Tomomyza pictipennis (lectotype in MSNM). 17, male habitus. 18, wing. 19 – 20. Exoprosopa fuscescens Bezzi (lectotype in MSNM). 19, female habitus. 20, wing. 21 – 22. Exoprosopa contorta (lectotype in BMNH). 21, female habitus. 22, wing." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[450,481,1499,1525]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad with anal lobe twice width of anal cell. Costal hook and comb black. Veins brown, membrane infuscated brown, paler at centres of cells. Apex from end of subcostal and posterior halves of cells m 
<number box="[816,827,1579,1605]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
, m 
<number box="[869,883,1579,1605]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
and cua 
<number box="[997,1007,1579,1605]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
clear. Crossvein r­m just beyond middle of discal cell, r 
<number box="[633,647,1619,1645]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
narrowed towards wing margin, crossvein m­m straight and oblique to wing margin, cell m 
<number box="[675,689,1659,1685]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
very long originating less than the length of r­m from apex of bm. Squama and fringe blackish brown. Haltere dark brown with apex of knob yellow­brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,899,1885]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Abdomen black with second and third terga obscurely brown at sides. Hair short black, scales black except for a pair of white scale spots at sides of second tergum and a few white scales at the sides of third tergum. Acanthophorite spines gleaming brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[312,885,284,310]" box="[312,885,284,310]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Length of body, 
<quantity box="[505,634,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="15.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="12.0">12–19 mm</quantity>
; of wing, 
<quantity box="[751,881,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="13.0">13–19 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
